Create a second .NET 9 class-library backend that returns the weather for a given city. Validate the incoming JWT from the request context using the exact same signing key, issuer, and audience as the authentication service.

The weather data comes from an external graft at https://dotnetweatherapi.onrender.com/ — inspect its published contract first, consume it through its official graft package (don't hand-write an HTTP/SDK client), and map its response to a simple flat DTO exposing the fields the frontend needs (such as city, country, temperature, condition, humidity, wind, and last-updated).

Make sure graft packages restore correctly during the Docker build, and host the service via gg with the same browser-JWT options as the other service. Add it to docker-compose.yml on ports 8081:80 and its HTTP/2 endpoint on 8990:8989.

Just implement, don't run.
